description:
#VEGAN Pork Sinigang sa Rattan fruit. For the pork, I used meat magic, and the fat is made of tapioca starch, rice flour, and agar. For the broth, its soured by rattan fruit. Have you heard of it? It has a sour flavor with hints of sweetness, like green tamarind. I also used mushroom broth for the umami. And, of course, lots of veggies. Very comforting soup!

For the Sinigang recipe, its in the book, Filipino Vegan, and for the pork recipe, its on my recorded livestream on Facebook (in the Nilaga episode). 

Kain na, lets eat! 

#astigvegan #filipinofood #filipinovegan #veganfilipino
